          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4">The <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-22-01-2025-h1-1-stock-markets-rallied" target="_blank">stock market rallied</a> on Tuesday in hopes of Trump delaying tariffs on China, Mexico, and Canada. The S&P 500 gained 0.9%, while the Russell 2000 closed up 1.9% at the end of the day. Space stocks gained substantially as Trump pledged to expand US space exploration efforts. Intuitive Machines surged by 24%, and Rocket Lab gained a substantial 30% by the end of the trading day. However, EV stocks closed in red after Trump issued guidance on a review of subsidies given to EV companies. The Bloomberg Electric Vehicles Index fell 1.2%. Rivian and Lucid Group also posted losses. The market remains dependent on Trump’s policy decisions in the short term.</p>
