            <strong>🇪🇬 Egypt bonds rally on ceasefire and Trump’s return</strong>
          </p>
          <p style="font-size:16px;line-height:1.4;">
          Egypt’s sovereign bonds rallied on Tuesday, driven by optimism around Trump's return to the presidency. The country is expected to benefit from the ceasefire in Gaza, which will lead to higher revenues from the Suez Canal as tensions in the Red Sea ease. Interest rate hikes and a currency devaluation have made Egypt’s bonds attractive to investors as they pile in multi-billion dollar inflows. However, the near-term outlook for Egypt remains uncertain as the country faces significant external funding needs. The country has a $1.5 billion bond maturing in June and another $750 million due in October. The government is expected to raise $3 billion by June (<a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-22-01-2025-wn1-3-egypt-bond-raise" target="_blank">Egypt bond raise</a>).
          </p>
