          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Apple shares drop on analyst downgrades:</strong> Apple has had a <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-22-01-2025-m1-6-rough-start-to-2025" target="_blank">rough start to 2025</a>, with the shares falling 3.2% on Tuesday. The company’s stock received downgrades by Loop Capital and Jefferies. Apple is facing a soft demand outlook for iPhones, especially in China. Moreover, the analysts believe US consumers have not found AI features compelling, potentially delaying an upgrade cycle. Apple is set to report its Q1 results next week.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Apple's iPhone sales drop 18% in China:</strong> Apple’s iPhone sales <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-22-01-2025-m2-7-plummeted-in-china" target="_blank">plummeted in China</a> in December, according to Counterpoint Research. The company’s sales fell by 18.2% during the month, losing its top-selling position to Huawei Technologies. Apple now holds the third place in China with a market share of around 16%. The weak demand in China has weighed on the stock’s performance and contributed to a global 5% drop in iPhone sales during the holiday shopping season.</p>
        </mj-text>
        <mj-text padding="10px 12px" font-family="Roboto+Serif" color="#000000">
          <p style="font-size: 16px; line-height: 1.4;"><span style="font-size:20px; padding-right:5px;">→</span><strong>Meta lures TikTok creators with incentives:</strong> Meta is attempting to lure TikTok creators to join its platform as TikTok faces an uncertain future in the US. The company announced <a href="https://link.longandshort.com/ls-22-01-2025-m3-8-creators-could-earn" target="_blank">creators could earn</a> up to $5,000 in bonuses over three months by posting Reels on Facebook and Instagram. Meta is ramping up efforts to improve its features on Reels to attract US-based content creators. The company also plans to launch a CapCut-like video editing app called Edits next month.</p>
